item.title: **Project Fnatic- Professional and most perfect 06 remake~ Vbulletin~ [ BETA ]
item.dc:creator: @ponypony ponypony
item.description:
@ponypony wrote:

I am posting on behalf of one my friends who plays on the server often. She doesn’t think its a big deal but doesn’t feel as comfortable logging on the server anymore (I am trying to get her to stop). The owner of the server apparently banned her for a few hours while we were watching movies. She had the game window small enough where only the spell logo thingys where open and since she had thousands of law runes thought if we watched a movie while she plays her stupid server (while clicking away) it would be fine since it is not automated. The owner logged on and said hi to her. She noticed and said hi back, and explained the she was watching a movie. The game then logged out so I convinced her just to put the movie on full screen (she was tired of clicking anyways). I went home for few moments and came back and we played cards. She got bored and logged on the game for a few moments and I guess the owner was mad at her for “autoing” and banned her for a few hours. He told her to look on the website for the rules. So she did and could not find the link to them. She then asked me tohelp her find the rules and I thought it was a little wierd then she showed me the message tab with the mod and at first I thought it was a joke because she was talking to the owner while clicking on things. so I decided to help find it since I am better with computers than her most of the time. There was no link to the game rules anywhere. She asked in game where there were on the website. The owner was on but didnt respond and so one of the other mods said where it was. We went to the section and all it was, was forum rules. She went back on and asked if there a different section for rules and nope. All the mod said was “what is done is done”.

People there are a LOT better servers out there with CLEAR rules that will not BAN you because you are watching movies. Honestly, I dont know how she got a bunch of law runes, but if this server is going to give its players a large number of an item that takes a lot of clicking to use and then ban you for “autoing” after after speaking with said player. They can at the very least have a section for the rules. Even so, she was not automating anything on this server.

I also gave the server a try and within 5 minutes the players were some of the meanest ones I have come across (I play minecraft) Do yourselves a favor and skip this server. My friend could do much better.
